sentences: Durga was born in Kumbakonam, Tamil Nadu on 1 June 1940 to S. A. Venkatarama Iyer and Lalithabai.
On completion of her postgraduate degree, she worked as a lecturer at the university from 1976 to 1979.
On 8 March 1984, she performed at a celebration marking the 150th anniversary of Wesleyan University.
In 1984, Durga was awarded the Eleanor Roosevelt International Fellowship of International Federation of University of Women.

sentences: S. A. Kumari Durga (1 June 1940 – 20 November 2016) was a musicologist and ethnomusicologist from the Indian state of Tamil Nadu.

Durga served as the Professor Emeritus of the Department of Indian music at the University of Madras for four years and founded the centre of Ethnomusicology in Chennai and currently serves as its director.
